article.headline: Tulane 76, UAB 73 (OT)
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored a career-high 24 points to lead Winthrop to a 65-57 victory over UAB on Wednesday. Winthrop (13-5, 4-1 Big South Conference) trailed 25-23 at halftime but shot 57 percent from the floor in the second half, including nine of 10 from beyond the arc to take control of the game in the final three minutes. James Shuler scored 15 points for the Eagles and hit two 3-pointers in the final minutes to lock the fourth straigh win for Winthrop. Martin also led the team in 3-point shots. The Eagles made 11-of-21 3-pointers, four of those by Martin. Jakob Sigurdarson scored a game-high 29 points for Birmingham-Southern (8-8, 1-4) and hit 4-of-5 shots from 3-point range. The Panthers consistently shot 50 percent from 3-point range throughout the game, hitting 8-of-16 3-pointers.
